@inject NavigationManager nvt

<div class="container-xxl py-5">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row g-0 gx-5 align-items-end">
            <div class="text-start mx-auto mb-5 wow slideInLeft" data-wow-delay="0.1s">
                <h1 class="mb-3">Manoj Pant</h1>
                <h4>
                    "Welcome to my website – Where Innovation Meets Elegance! Discover a world of limitless possibilities as we redefine [Your Industry/Niche]. Immerse yourself in a seamless blend of cutting-edge technology and unparalleled style. Our commitment to excellence ensures an extraordinary experience for every visitor. Explore, engage, and elevate your journey with [Your Brand]. Join us in shaping the future, one click at a time. Your adventure begins here!"

                    Feel free to adjust the text based on the specific features, services, or products your website offers, and the tone you want to convey to your audience.Creating a great portfolio can be hard when you’re focused on getting more work experience. Yet, it's important that you set some time to craft your own personal portfolio. Whether you’re a UI designer, user experience designer, web designer, graphic designer, or marketer, having your own portfolio website will help you bring more visibility to your work and allow you to attract new clients..
                </h4>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="image-container">
        <img src="Libraries/img/CodeImg.jpg" class="small-image" />
    </div>


    <style>
        body {
            background-color: thistle;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            font-family: Calibri;
        }

        .image-container {
            text-align: right; /* Align the content to the right */
        }

        .small-image {
            max-width: 500px; /* Set the maximum width */
            max-height: 500px; /* Set the maximum height */
            width: inherit; /* Maintain aspect ratio */
            height: auto; /* Maintain aspect ratio */
            align-content: flex-end;
        }

        h1 {
            color: black; /* Set text color */
            font-size: 2em; /* Set font size */
            font-weight: bold; /* Set font weight */
            text-align: left;
        }
    </style>
    <br />
    <br />
    <img src="Libraries/img/CoderImg.jpg" class="small-image" />
    <br />
    <br />
    <div class="col-12 text-center wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.1s">
        <a class="btn btn-primary py-3 px-5" @onclick="MoreDetails">Browse More Details</a>
    </div>
</div>

@code {
    void MoreDetails()
    {
        nvt.NavigateTo("moredetails");
    }
}

